Introduced Version
SENATE BILL No. 141
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 24-4.7.
Synopsis: Administration of do not call list. Requires a monthly listing
of telephone numbers of Indiana consumers who request not to be
solicited by telephone to be established, maintained, and published
(current law requires a quarterly listing). Provides that certain actions
may not be brought more than five years after the occurrence of the
deceptive act (current law provides that the action may not be brought
more than two years after the occurrence of the deceptive act). Makes
conforming changes.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Becker
January 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Judiciary.
